    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-11-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="722"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d722">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-11-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 30, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Sultan desires President’s approval for me to send consul of the United
                    States to Sasoun, with Turkish commission to investigate alleged atrocities on
                    Armenians. I believe your consent will result in great benefit to missionaries
                    in Asia Minor. He wishes the presence of a representative of a neutral power and
                    selects the United States of America. Sends his compliments to the President. I
                    would select Jewett. The Sultan requests a reply before Monday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
